CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 7, 1965, pg. 22, reads: "Champions - Shown above are members of the Cardinals, newly crowned champions of the Homewood - Brushton Atehletic [Athletic] Association Little League. Left to right, front row: D. Thompson, K. Thompson, William King, D. James, G. Meachum and Richard Britton.  Second row:  H. Trent, D. Jenkins, J. Paxton, E. Graves, R. Fox, D. Ragland, B. Terry, R. Fluker and Troy Steward, coach.  Rear: Gerald Fox, manager, and Val Cherry, president of the HBAA. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Homewood Little League Cardinals "Cards" baseball team, front row from left: Kevin Thompson, Darryl Thompson, William King, D. James, G. Meachum, Richard Britton, H. Trent, D. Jenkins, J. Paxton, E. Graves, Richard C. Fox Sr., D. Ragland, B. Terry, R. Fluker, coach Troy Steward; rear: manager Gerald W. Fox, and Val Cherry, posed in front of William "Woogie" Harris' house, 7101 Apple Street, with woman lying on hillside in background
